Description: Lip and wall sherd (mended from two fragments, including 1886,0401.850) of East Greek (North Ionian) pottery rosette bowl; interior glazed dark brown with added red band lined in white; exterior: dot-rosette below rim, narrow stripe at top of lip; inscription cut on exterior.
Findspot: Excavated/Findspot: Sanctuary of Apollo (Naukratis), temenos (said to be)
Curator's comments: Joins 1886,0401.850. Probably not from same bowl as 1888,0401.870.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GG.836)
